variables.definition: Country in which study was conducted

Gaining control studies were conducted in areas of >25% S. mansoni prevalence in Kenya and Tanzania. Sustaining control studies were conducted in areas of 10-24% S. mansoni prevalence in Cote d'Ivoire and Kenya.

Abbreviation refers to community-level treatment in each of four study years. Gaining studies were conducted in areas of >25% S. mansoni prevalence and Sustaining studies in areas of 10-24% prevalence. s=school based treatment, c= community wide treatment, h=drug holiday.

Presence or absence of Ascaris lumbricoides infection in a study participant, based on detection of at least one parasite egg in any of the stool samples. Up to three stool samples were collected per participant on consecutive days. Two slides were prepared from each stool sample using the Kato-Katz method and examined by light microscopy for parasite eggs.
